Review text: "When my Sequoias engine died, I paid cash for an inexpensive 2002 Nissan Xterra. It had low miles and drove great, but the interior was a bit depressing. The Xterra was meant to be temporary until I could find what I really wanted. I didnt mind driving it but I missed the nice, comfortable interior of my Sequoia. I wondered how differently I would feel about the Xterra if I could make it more enjoyable to be in. So I bought these seat covers and some other accessories.  The covers fit like they are custom-made for the seats and headrests. It took only a few minutes to put them on. I was worried that the covers would shift when I got in and out of the car and that I would be constantly readjusting them.  This is not the case.  I was also worried that the seats would feel hot but that isnt happening either.  They (along with the other items I have purchased) have completely transformed the look and feel of my Xterras interior and have made the car more pleasurable to drive. In fact, Im no longer looking for another vehicle.  I included several images. One includes a tiny plastic bag with metal hooks you will need to attach to elastic bands that are on each side of the seat covers. Youll add the hooks to the bands and attach the hooks to each other under the seat. Im mentioning this because the bag is so tiny, it could easily be overlooked.  I cant report on the durability of the seat covers as they have only been in use for a week. I will report back after a few months.  For the price, Ill be happy if I can get a year out of them. I would happily reorder and definitely recommend them."

I purchased my Mustang in 2006 and my gray leather drivers seat has worn and split in a few places, especially on the side of the seat, to the point of the foam bulging through.  Ive tried other seat covers as a cover up, but NOTHING compared to these.  I needed my entire seat covered and not a pad on the front seat that flips to the back of the seat. They fit snug and do not move; they are plush and very very comfortable.  The back of the seat goes on like a tee-shirt and snaps under the head rest and zips on the side at the bottom.  The seat goes on like a cap/hat and covers the sides an front, then the elastic cords pull under the seats and connect to lock them in place.  They look much better in person than in my pics, it was hard to get a good angle.  I hope this company will always have these seat covers around!"

Review text:
Such a cute idea!  

Not gaudy but just adds a little sparkle to your vehicle.  

My friend was riding in my truck and noticed them from the back seat and she immediately said she wants some.  

Very easy to install - I just pulled the headrest off and popped these on the poles and put it back on.  

You really do want to have the headrest all the way down or they will rattle and kind of drive you crazy.  

Once I put it all the way down that fixed that problem and no more rattling.

Review text: The media could not be loaded.                , 'xa0I purchased these seat covers for my 2023 Honda CRV Hybrid Sport to protect my cloth seats from dirt and mainly from absorbing sweat when leaving the gym and so I can wipe them down to sanitize. Well they really are a custom fit! They look like original leather seats and the quality is really soft and great! I know someone in another review mentioned theirs did not come with the cutouts for back seat reclining handles but mine did and I provided a photo. One of my issues with these is the texture against clothing! I can’t just slide in and out of my car like in a normal leather seated car because your clothes stick and will tug the seat covers and makes them shift and I have to keep adjusting them back to place and some of the hooks under the seats keep coming undone and I have to hook them again. Also the seat covers come in 2 pieces, one for the back rest and one for seat and they don’t really meet or over lap so if I were to accidentally spill a liquid on the seat it will spill towards the back where the back rest and seat meet and soak into your cloth seats underneath (also provided pic of the gap for reference). I also included a video of how to access the back seat cup holder. Overall I think these are great seat covers for my car and my needs. I am leaving a detailed review that I would’ve liked to see when looking for seat covers so you can make a decision about these before purchasing. $250 is a little steep but cheaper than having to pay a detailer to shampoo your seats in the future and to keep buying those crappy covers from auto stores that never fit right and rip easily. I would give 5 stars but the tugging with my clothing is annoying that I have to practically hop into and out of the car. I will try a leather lotion and see if that helps🤷🏽'u200d♀️

Review text: I bought two of the Carbella Sequin Tweed Carseat Cover(s) in Beige to cover my uncomfortable leather seats. Leather is so gross. I’m really happy with the look of these covers. The color is not beige. It’s like the picture, so it is tan tweed; darker than beige. The fabric isn’t itchy like real tweed, nor is it high quality. It’s not soft, but it’s comfortable, even on bare skin. I haven’t had them long enough to speak on durability, but I can see them ripping eventually. The sequins are great! They really do sparkle in all kinds of light. The sequins are also not sharp or scratchy like other sequins can be. They’re tiny and reflective. I love how the designer took a less us more approach with the sequins. They’re pretty but not gaudy., The only problem is that the seat covers are too big. My vehicle is a minivan with roomy captain seats and they tend to pop off the sides and just don’t look as taught as I would like them to look. I’m keeping them anyway, because I do love the color and the sequins. I will try to finagle a solution to the looseness.

Review text: This is a review of the car seat cover for rear of tesla. Other than this part, it is ok and it is partially an exact fit. As you can see on the image, the seat is rectangle and did not conform to the bucket like seat. After securing the upper part to the headrest, it is somewhat contoured to the upper back seat which gives this somewhat of an ok design for something that is custom made for tesla. For its price, I think I would not ask for more at this point. The material feels tough and can withstand doggy nails. It feels waterproof and easy to clean and this should catch every spill and crumbs from my kids. It will keep my original seats in its pristine condition while giving me a peace of mind that then can eat whatever they want without the me having an anxiety. If you have someone that will not take care of your rear seats, this is a good investment. It does not look luxurious but people will understand.

For its price, I think I would not ask for more at this point. The material feels tough and can withstand doggy nails. It feels waterproof and easy to clean and this should catch every spill and crumbs from my kids. It will keep my original seats in its pristine condition while giving me a peace of mind that then can eat whatever they want without the me having an anxiety. If you have someone that will not take care of your rear seats, this is a good investment. It does not look luxurious but people will understand.

This is my first time not using a universal sized pet liner and I can say that getting one that is fitted for your car makes a difference. The top layer is not as soft as I would like. The two features I love the most about this liner are the velcro covers for the seat belt buckle that prevents fur from getting under the line when the seat belt isn’t being used and the zipper for the middle arm rest which allows you to use the arm rest without having to remove the liner. My biggest complaint is the liner doesn’t come with a dog seat belt.

This is my first time not using a universal sized pet liner and I can say that getting one that is fitted for your car makes a difference. The top layer is not as soft as I would like. The two features I love the most about this liner are the velcro covers for the seat belt buckle that prevents fur from getting under the line when the seat belt isn’t being used and the zipper for the middle arm rest which allows you to use the arm rest without having to remove the liner. My biggest complaint is the liner doesn’t come with a dog seat belt.

The headrest cover was decent, and the seatback portion fit very tautly, looked great! Only the seat bottom showed much sign of sagginess, though not bad enough to be objectionable, not to me. The workmanship was surprisingly good, especially for such a budget priced product. The seams straight, stitching excellent, with only one loose thread on the entire cover (snip!). Generally Im a guy who stretches an old XL T-shirt over the seat back and throws an old towel on the seat bottom, but these seat covers are an elegant and affordable alternative."

Review text: I looked around at many different options for a faux leather, pleather, etc... style seat cover.  I like the stitching and piping on these seat covers.  I also like the breathable texture and styling of the front seat covers.  There is a zipper on the side of the front seat covers to help with installation.  The fastening features are pretty good for the back piece however the bottom portion of the cover hangs loose and is not not snug to the seat.  I ended up using some velcro (although double sided sticky tape may work) to secure the back of the cover to give the back passengers more comfort and keep them from being kicked or damaged.  The butt piece for the front seat fits securely, it took some time but I was able to get it to fit snugly with the provided fasteners., "The center storage area cover seems more like a throw in and is only held in place by three elastic straps. The upper portion of the rear seat cover is little more than a blanket with well placed fasteners to hold it place.  They do not slide over the rear seats. There is no cut out for the center armrest, however there are zippers on either side of the center part of the back rest.  Not a big deal to remove that piece but these are supposed to be fit for my 2018 Ram Rebel and are not as advertised.  They also dont stay true when I fold the bench out of the way.  The butt portion for the rear seat covers is nice and will do well over time, I hope...  The rear head rest covers are just pieces of faux material that fold over the headrest. The material feels nice and upon installation looks nice too.  The front seats look as good as the pictures, just take your time and put on some gloves, I cut my hands a couple few times finding a spot for the front butt piece cover fasteners...

Review text: I have a 2023 Ram 1500 Big Horn Quad Cab and these are what the seat covers look like in my truck. Instructions are definitely not updated with the 2023 trucks as there is a metal backing plate between the seats and the fabric preventing you from being able to pull anything through to the other side. They seem to get the job done and feel pretty solid. Just wish there was a bit more transparency in the fact that only the front seat sections were full coverage. They are comfortable, will update on durability as time goes on. I’m in AZ so definitely curious as to how they will hold up with the heat.

Review text: I looked around at many different options for a faux leather, pleather, etc... style seat cover.  I like the stitching and piping on these seat covers.  I also like the breathable texture and styling of the front seat covers.  There is a zipper on the side of the front seat covers to help with installation.  The fastening features are pretty good for the back piece however the bottom portion of the cover hangs loose and is not not snug to the seat.  I ended up using some velcro (although double sided sticky tape may work) to secure the back of the cover to give the back passengers more comfort and keep them from being kicked or damaged.  The butt piece for the front seat fits securely, it took some time but I was able to get it to fit snugly with the provided fasteners., "The center storage area cover seems more like a throw in and is only held in place by three elastic straps.  Its loose and doesnt fit snugly.  I may end up trying to find another way to fasten it but will likely just toss it.", "The rear seat covers are the reason I gave this product a 3 star rating.  The upper portion of the rear seat cover is little more than a blanket with well placed fasteners to hold it place.  They do not slide over the rear seats.  They just lay over the upper portion of the seat with elastic bands and clips around the head rests.  There is no cut out for the center armrest, however there are zippers on either side of the center part of the back rest.  Not a big deal to remove that piece but these are supposed to be fit for my 2018 Ram Rebel and are not as advertised.  They also dont stay true when I fold the bench out of the way.  The butt portion for the rear seat covers is nice and will do well over time, I hope...  The rear head rest covers are just pieces of faux material that fold over the headrest.  Not full surrounds like the front head rests, and that was disappointing considering the same amount of material could have been used instead of a floppy, sloppy center counsel cover.", "There were some areas of piping that were not stitched and shouldnt have made it past quality control.  I may end up stiching that myself with a needle and thread.", The fronts were the most important part as its my truck and thats where I stay.  The material feels nice and upon installation looks nice too.  The front seats look as good as the pictures, just take your time and put on some gloves, I cut my hands a couple few times finding a spot for the front butt piece cover fasteners...

Review text: "Bought for my 2023 TRD sport. This came with some sticker residue on some of the seats but I was able to remove it with nail polish remover. These covers were definitely not as easy to install as I was hoping. The install video makes it look easy and takes 15min to watch. Actual install took me over 2hrs. Difficult to get under the seats to clip covers and took some strength to get back seat covers on tight. But once completed they look very nice overall. I like that they provide full coverage. I do wish back seat covers for the bottom seat portion came with straps because they will come loose and need to be readjusted if you plan on lifting the back seats to get to the storage compartment under the seat. The drivers seat was also a little difficult to push cover material under the plastic that is near the controls of the seat and the front underside. The one thing that disappointed me most was that one headrest was stitched wrong. See picture attached how the stitching is different on one headrest compared to the other. I tried putting it on backwards but it did not fit that way. If I could get a replacement that would be nice. I also wish the trim edges were leather and not the burgundy fabric to make it look more real and luxurious. I did not install the center console cover as I felt that part looked the most fake and cheap. Could have a better fit. Lastly, red is more of a muted warm orangey red than a true bold red. Overall after installation, these covers look pretty nice and most wouldnt notice it is just a cover at first glance."

Review text: "Bought for my 2023 TRD sport. This came with some sticker residue on some of the seats but I was able to remove it with nail polish remover. These covers were definitely not as easy to install as I was hoping. The install video makes it look easy and takes 15min to watch. Actual install took me over 2hrs. Difficult to get under the seats to clip covers and took some strength to get back seat covers on tight. But once completed they look very nice overall. I like that they provide full coverage. I do wish back seat covers for the bottom seat portion came with straps because they will come loose and need to be readjusted if you plan on lifting the back seats to get to the storage compartment under the seat. The drivers seat was also a little difficult to push cover material under the plastic that is near the controls of the seat and the front underside. The one thing that disappointed me most was that one headrest was stitched wrong. See picture attached how the stitching is different on one headrest compared to the other. I tried putting it on backwards but it did not fit that way. If I could get a replacement that would be nice. I also wish the trim edges were leather and not the burgundy fabric to make it look more real and luxurious. I did not install the center console cover as I felt that part looked the most fake and cheap. Could have a better fit. Lastly, red is more of a muted warm orangey red than a true bold red. Overall after installation, these covers look pretty nice and most wouldnt notice it is just a cover at first glance."

Review text: "I have a 1979 F-150 that I welded new floor panels in to get rid of the fred flintstone style floor it had when I acquired the truck back in November.  Put some new vinyl flooring in too and needed something to cover up the worn out 42 year old upholstery.  I wanted the old saddle blanket style seat cover in blue to match the rest of the truck but wasnt having much luck finding one locally.  Amazon to the rescue!  I cant speak for trying to install this with the seat in the truck since I had the seat out to work on the floors.  I can see how this would be very difficult if not impossible to install correctly with the seat in the truck.  Starting with the back in the middle I tied one string at a time and tried to make an X pattern with the strings where possible.  I worked from the middle out and left the sides loose.  Moved to the bottom of the seat, same as before, worked my way from the middle out to the sides forming an X where possible with the strings.  I then visually inspected the everything to make sure the pattern was straight and the back and bottom were aligned.  Once confirmed everything looked good there, I moved on to tightening the sides down by tying off the strings I had already tightened for the bottom and back.", No this does not have full coverage of the back, but I have a standard cab pickup so the only time you see that is when you need to retrieve something from behind the seat.  If you have a super or crew cab and the back of the seat is going to be seen often you may want to look for a different solution if that bothers you., "I didnt need to add any string and though you can tell this string isnt 100# test or 550 para cord it is working okay so far.  I also didnt tighten the strings down like I was trying to stretch raw hide over a snare drum either so that might have helped too."

Review text: These bright red seat covers with black accents look very nice in my Ford Escape hybrid.  They have an igneous mounting system using black plastic discs which slide through elastic straps then are pushed through where the seat back reclines and meets the seat bottom.  After many trips there is no indication this system will loosen or slip out over time.  The seat bottom front is affixed with similar elastic strips that affix to hooks that can be attached underneath the seat.  I had to be careful placing these since Ford has some sharp metal edges under the seat, so you may want to wear some gloves for that part of the installation. The headrest covers attach with snaps and complete the appearance nicely.  We found that the additional included neck braces that loop around the head rest were not necessary for us, so we removed them.  The car seat heaters work exactly the same without any noticeable difference in warmth.  Overall, these are really nice and have a clean look that will personalize your vehicle and protect the factory seats from damage.

Review text: "OK, so maybe these are a bit cheesy, but I was celebrating no longer having to share a car, that I wanted to do something out of the box fun with it.  I didnt know it was getting these until I was browsing and found them!  I have a 22 Chevy Equinox with heated leather front seats.  The covers come in 2 parts, and are pretty easy to get on, but not as easy to secure them to the seat.  Which one should expect, as not all cars front seats are the same.  So, there was some tugging involved, and possibly even a few PG-13 phrases were thrown around.  Innovation and creativity take over and you figure out how to make it work with what you have.  The fur is warmer for sure when you just get into the car, but I do think that the warmth takes longer to reach your body with the covers on than just the leather.  So, its a trade-off that you have to decide on.  Im going to see how these keep performing for me, but so far, I love them!"

Review text: "I bought 2 new cars in 2023.  One has a leather seats.  The other has cloth seats.  This is the first time Ive had cloth seats in at least 20 years but Im loving the cloth in hot or cold weather.  Except.....", My female companion took my car to go pick up some takeout food (Indian) on a Saturday night.  She placed the bag of food on the cloth passenger seat. It took about a half hour to clean the seat while our dinner was getting cold., "OK, lesson learned.  I never drink coffee or eat anything in my cars as a general rule.  My female companion has learned her lesson about putting foods on the cloth seats.  But... Would protect just the front seat cushions including both the horizontal and vertical surfaces., 2.) Can be installed and removed quickly and easily., 3.) Looks acceptable., "4.) Doesnt cost a fortune.", 5.) Is reasonably durable., "These seat covers do everything I want.  They cover all of the front seat cushions on all surfaces that could reasonably be expected to be exposed to a spill or dropped food.  It takes less that 5 minutes to install both covers. At $20 apiece, the price is well worth it to me if it saves the interior of a new car from stains and smells while eliminating cleaning time for me.  And lastly, I only intend to have these covers installed occasionally during road trips when I know Im gonna have food and drink in the car.  Other than that, theyll just live in the trunk because I like the feel of the cloth seats.  So durability should be good enough for a $20 seat cover.  But even if I used them every day and they wear out in a year, $40 a year to protect a new cars interior isnt a bad deal in my mind.", The other question that crossed my mind was "will the seat covers interfere with the seat heaters"?  They probably do a little.  Maybe a slight delay in the heat reaching your butt.  But it doesn't seem that annoying to me. Review text: "I bought 2 new cars in 2023.  One has a leather seats.  The other has cloth seats.  This is the first time Ive had cloth seats in at least 20 years but Im loving the cloth in hot or cold weather.  Except.....", My female companion took my car to go pick up some takeout food (Indian) on a Saturday night.  She placed the bag of food on the cloth passenger seat. It took about a half hour to clean the seat while our dinner was getting cold., "OK, lesson learned.  I never drink coffee or eat anything in my cars as a general rule.  My female companion has learned her lesson about putting foods on the cloth seats.  But... I will have coffee and a sandwich occasionally when Im on a road trip and in the car for 4-8 hours.", So I wanted something that....., 1.) Would protect just the front seat cushions including both the horizontal and vertical surfaces., 2.) Can be installed and removed quickly and easily., 3.) Looks acceptable., "4.) Doesnt cost a fortune.", 5.) Is reasonably durable., "These seat covers do everything I want.  They cover all of the front seat cushions on all surfaces that could reasonably be expected to be exposed to a spill or dropped food.  It takes less that 5 minutes to install both covers.  They look pretty low key and unobtrusive.  Yeah theyre vinyl.  But they fit pretty well and the design doesnt draw a lot of attention.  They look fine.  At $20 apiece, the price is well worth it to me if it saves the interior of a new car from stains and smells while eliminating cleaning time for me.  And lastly, I only intend to have these covers installed occasionally during road trips when I know Im gonna have food and drink in the car.  Other than that, theyll just live in the trunk because I like the feel of the cloth seats.  So durability should be good enough for a $20 seat cover.  But even if I used them every day and they wear out in a year, $40 a year to protect a new cars interior isnt a bad deal in my mind.", The other question that crossed my mind was "will the seat covers interfere with the seat heaters"?  They probably do a little.  Maybe a slight delay in the heat reaching your butt.  But it doesn't seem that annoying to me.  The seat still heats up and reaches my butt reasonably fast., "So all in all, Im happy with these seat covers.  They achieve exactly what I wanted for a very reasonable cost."

Review text: "I bought 2 new cars in 2023.  One has a leather seats.  The other has cloth seats.  This is the first time Ive had cloth seats in at least 20 years but Im loving the cloth in hot or cold weather.  Except.....", My female companion took my car to go pick up some takeout food (Indian) on a Saturday night.  She placed the bag of food on the cloth passenger seat.  When she lifted the bag to leave the car, she realized one of the containers had leaked....through the bag and onto the cloth seat.  It took about a half hour to clean the seat while our dinner was getting cold., "OK, lesson learned.  I never drink coffee or eat anything in my cars as a general rule.  My female companion has learned her lesson about putting foods on the cloth seats.  But... I will have coffee and a sandwich occasionally when Im on a road trip and in the car for 4-8 hours.", So I wanted something that....., 1.) Would protect just the front seat cushions including both the horizontal and vertical surfaces., 2.) Can be installed and removed quickly and easily., 3.) Looks acceptable., "4.) Doesnt cost a fortune.", 5.) Is reasonably durable., "These seat covers do everything I want.  They cover all of the front seat cushions on all surfaces that could reasonably be expected to be exposed to a spill or dropped food.  It takes less that 5 minutes to install both covers.  They look pretty low key and unobtrusive.  Yeah theyre vinyl.  But they fit pretty well and the design doesnt draw a lot of attention.  They look fine.  At $20 apiece, the price is well worth it to me if it saves the interior of a new car from stains and smells while eliminating cleaning time for me.  And lastly, I only intend to have these covers installed occasionally during road trips when I know Im gonna have food and drink in the car.  Other than that, theyll just live in the trunk because I like the feel of the cloth seats.  So durability should be good enough for a $20 seat cover.  But even if I used them every day and they wear out in a year, $40 a year to protect a new cars interior isnt a bad deal in my mind.", The other question that crossed my mind was "will the seat covers interfere with the seat heaters"?  They probably do a little.  Maybe a slight delay in the heat reaching your butt.  But it doesn't seem that annoying to me.  The seat still heats up and reaches my butt reasonably fast., "So all in all, Im happy with these seat covers.  They achieve exactly what I wanted for a very reasonable cost."

Review text: I own a new 2023 Toyota Corolla and was looking to protect my investment, especially since I will be having this car for awhile. I came across these "universal" car seat covers and decided to give these a try, even after trying many bad ones over the years. Once these arrived, I popped them right on and I have a love / hate relationship with them... but more love than hate., Love:, > The color of these seat covers match my stock interior colors pretty close!! Review text: I’ve purchased low-end seat covers at auto-stores before and they are usually quite thin and wear out quickly.  Seeing the CAT name on these seat covers had me thinking they were going to be of superior quality and would be more rugged … that was not the case., WHAT YOU GET, A pair of PU leather seat and headrest covers.  They are designed to be a universal fit for trucks/SUVs.  The box they are packed in has the installation instructions on the back., INSTALLATION AND QUALITY, The quality of these seat covers was evident the minute I had the box in my hands as the box seemed to weigh more than the contents.  I found these covers to be quite thin.  They are made of PU leather bordered by meshing with a thin layer of foam underneath.  Assembly is easy and simply involves removing the headrests, slipping the covers over the seat back, pushing a soft bar into the seat crevice and pulling the bottom over the seat.  While I had no issue with these fitting my 2015 Nissan Xterra, I did not like the flimsy nature and felt that the bar wedged into the seat crevice was insufficient in keeping the seat cover in place.  My current set of seat covers has disks that push through and prevent the seat covers from moving at all.  Additionally, the look and feel of the covers is not impressive.  The CAT logo just doesn’t support the quality of the covers … I was expecting something way more rugged., If you are looking for something simple to protect your seats, these may be sufficient.  But if you are expecting something rugged/durable … look elsewhere.

Review text: I got these seT covers for my Ford F250 pick up. It had been a company work truck before I bought it so the seats were pretty beat up. They fit OK, a little tight at the base of the seats and a little loose around the head rest but overall they look ok.  I found them to be a thinner material than expected but they feel nice when they are on the seats and I have used them for just over 2 weeks and they have stayed in place well and show no signs of wear or ripping at the seams. I will be interested to see how they hold up after a few months. The sides of the covers are made of a netting that does not make them look quality but does help with stretch and putting the co ears on. Also, I live in Texas where it has been 105 degrees daily and I feel like it helps the solid material cool off quicker and makes the sides of the seats not hot to the touch. There were also plenty of places made to attach the covers to the bottom of the truck seat to make the fit and stay in place, this was very helpful. I love the CAT logo and the interior of my truck is black and gray so the match very well. Overall an OK seat cover so far.

Review text: "Like most folks, I take pride in keeping my car as pristine as possible. From time to time, I would see a shiny spot, on the front of my drivers side headrest. That is where these YOLRIND headrest covers come into play. Therefore, when the opportunity presented itself, for me to get this pair, I did not hesitate. These universal covers are flexible, and breathable, and come with elastic bottoms, to ensure a tight fit. I understand that a tight fit is what is desired. However, the covers were not easy for me to get on, as the elastic bottoms seemed too small. But, once I wrestled them on, I did see the resulting tight fit. Additionally, the set was advertised as having two covers, with an embroidered logo, in the center. I was extremely disappointed, as the logo was not embroidered, but a silkscreen, like on a t-shirt. For now, I guess I will keep them on, as they will protect the headrests from dust, dirt, and normal wear and tear. However, I can invision the day that I will look at them as not up to standard, with the rest of the interior, and just remove them. If so, I will come back and update my review."

Review text: "Like most folks, I take pride in keeping my car as pristine as possible. From time to time, I would see a shiny spot, on the front of my drivers side headrest. For now, I guess I will keep them on, as they will protect the headrests from dust, dirt, and normal wear and tear. However, I can invision the day that I will look at them as not up to standard, with the rest of the interior, and just remove them. If so, I will come back and update my review."

Review text: "I decided to order this car seat cover because it was a free review item.  Plus I eat a lot in my SUV so this would offer protection for my seats.  Installation was easy. It came with instructions on how to put this on. But I have electric powered seats and my seats has covers on the back side. It has two straps that your suppose to slip between the back and the seat and at the end of the straps is a hexagon shape plastic that is suppose to hold it in place. So thats a no go for me. So I just inserted it between the cushions and hoped for the best. Now the sides of the covers I did manage to strap in place and squeeze it in between the cushion and the plastic cover of the seat. And for the back none of the straps I could put in place so I just place the seat covers on top since nobody sits in the back anyways. As far as protection and breathability it is really easy to clean up. I dropped mocha syrup on it drinking Starbucks and I just wiped it off clean. As far as anything red like wine that I dont know. So sitting on this right now has no problems of my legs sweating. Summer time comes that remains to be seen. So its on my seats but it does move so I have to constantly adjust it when I sit on it.  But I will go neutral on this review with 3 stars.  And let you decide. Like I said it didnt fit my Subaru Forester seats but it may fit your SUV or Car depends on the type of seats you  have. Review text: "These seat covers are definitely an upgrade from my factory interior. The inside of my car looks like a completely different vehicle. It looks awesome. These covers are comfortable, and waterproof. They come with a padded neck pillow that straps to the headrest and covers the gap between the headrest and the top of the seat. Those are my favorite parts. The gaps under the headrests have always bothered me, but on my car, they dont adjust. I am really happy about how these covers look, but putting them in was ridiculous. They dont come with the hooks attached. They come with a bag full of hooks and anchors that you have to put on as you install the covers. It was a lot of work, and was incredibly stressful. It took me almost an hour to get them all in. I like how they look, and I am happy that I did it. I am not sure I would go so far as to say it was worth all of that, though. I literally had to get a babysitter just to be able to install these. Thats how ridiculous it was to put these in. These covers are designed to fit most cars, trucks and SUVs, and they come with hooks and elastic straps to secure them in place. The product description is confusing stating theyre made of leather. Review text: In terms of materials and such, these are fantastic.  Good layering, good stitching, the whole nine., For reference, this went into my 2011 Mercedes C300 project car.  Because yes, the W204 seats WILL wear out., First, the front.  Fit was very good considering the "one size fits most" design.  Really, the only improvisation needed was in finding a place to secure the S hooks.  And I say improvisation because the printed instructions are...less than ideal.  There's a video which helped but in reality, it's not too demanding to figure out how to get these installed.  The effort was rewarded by seats that looked brand new., At least in the front., "The back covers, on the other hand, need some compromise on the part of the owner.  They are much more finicky and much less adaptable than the front.  For example, my car has a fold-out arm rest in the back, something the design of this cover does not allow for.  Its covered by a third piece that attaches to the two side pieces covering the actual seats.  Doing away with the middle piece means the side pieces arent attached to each other and creates an unfinished look.  While I suppose its possible to modify the center piece and cut a hole in it...thats not a workable solution either.  Overall installation of the back covers was also significantly more frustrating than the front (for instance, the instructions tell you to secure the S hooks to the cushion bottoms, but that requires removal of the cushions on many cars.....).  Improvisation is again required, but the result is less than ideal, especially if youre OCD.", "So in sum, Id say that the front covers are very good, but the back covers are quite a bit more limiting.  On balance I like these covers, but for those who make regular use of the back seat, the impression will be somewhat less than anticipated."

Review text: My Honda Accord coupe ranks between sporty and ordinary, so I appreciate that the seat covers ramp up a spirited look with racing stripes and patterns.  They offer something of a leathery feel, smooth but not slick, fit comfortably, and come with an additional support pillow you can attach to the headrest.  Amazon has a handy confirmed fit feature where you enter the model of your car and it will advise you whether the seat cover can fit., While the instructions initially befuddled me, they do ultimately prove easy to install.  First, check which side has the side airbag cutout.  Most of my photos were taken before I noticed that, and I had to reinstall them.  The seat covers are held in place by disks.  All you do is slip the strap through the sides of the disk, insert it between the top and bottom of the seat, and twist it 90° so it grabs the seat.  The front bottom of the seat attaches with hooks underneath the seat., "For the side airbag, it uses stitching along one side to allow the airbag to deploy (see photo).  While Im unsure how well that will work in an accident, other manufacturers use similar methods to allow side airbag access without leaving a large gap in the cover.", "I havent used seat covers in years, and I consider the price rather high, but even more expensive seat covers sell quite well on Amazon.  Admittedly, most of the best-sellers, even some purporting to use leather, cost less than half of the price here, although few of the budget offerings deliver as much in the looks department.  These are excellent-looking seat covers that fit my car perfectly, and I could spend quite a lot more on seat covers if so inclined.  While in my mind, its not an exceptional value, it does deliver on what it purports to offer, a premium race car look and feel."

Review text: I ordered these seat covers for my 2018 Chevy Trax. I purchased just the front seat covers to replace one that was worn on the passenger side of my car. Straight out of the box, I was impressed with the quality material and sporty look of these seat covers. The fabric is heavy-duty, with a fairly thick foam and mesh backing that makes the seat covers feel more substantial. I was worried about whether the back and the head cushion sections would fit, but they fit my Trax perfectly. The head rest covers were quite snug and required some gentle pushing and wiggling back and forth, but with a bit of patience, I was able to get the material tight and then secure the snaps in place. The back covers slid right over the seats. These are airbag compatible, so they must be installed correctly to accommodate the airbag configuration of your car., The one minor issue I didn’t care for is the method of securing the seat covers in place. The bottom covers have two elastic straps in the front, and these attach to sturdy metal clips, which you stretch under the seat and hook on to any convenient anchor. Two elastic straps in the back slip through the seat gap, and then four straps from the upper cover also slip through the seat gap and are secured using plastic discs. Four discs are provided for each seat. The plastic seems heavy-duty enough that the discs shouldn’t break, but I would prefer to use metal hooks instead so that the elastic straps can be stretched a bit more, pulling the cover tight over the seat base. Still, the discs were quick and easy to install. The end result looks great and adds a sporty touch to my Chevy Trax.

Review text: My Honda Accord coupe ranks between sporty and ordinary, so I appreciate that the seat covers ramp up a spirited look with racing stripes and patterns.  They offer something of a leathery feel, smooth but not slick, fit comfortably, and come with an additional support pillow you can attach to the headrest.  Amazon has a handy confirmed fit feature where you enter the model of your car and it will advise you whether the seat cover can fit., While the instructions initially befuddled me, they do ultimately prove easy to install.  First, check which side has the side airbag cutout.  Most of my photos were taken before I noticed that, and I had to reinstall them.  The seat covers are held in place by disks.  All you do is slip the strap through the sides of the disk, insert it between the top and bottom of the seat, and twist it 90° so it grabs the seat.  The front bottom of the seat attaches with hooks underneath the seat., "For the side airbag, it uses stitching along one side to allow the airbag to deploy (see photo).  While Im unsure how well that will work in an accident, other manufacturers use similar methods to allow side airbag access without leaving a large gap in the cover.", "I havent used seat covers in years, and I consider the price rather high, but even more expensive seat covers sell quite well on Amazon.  Admittedly, most of the best-sellers, even some purporting to use leather, cost less than half of the price here, although few of the budget offerings deliver as much in the looks department.  These are excellent-looking seat covers that fit my car perfectly, and I could spend quite a lot more on seat covers if so inclined.  While in my mind, its not an exceptional value, it does deliver on what it purports to offer, a premium race car look and feel."

Review text: "I installed these seat covers in my ’22 Tacoma and have now been using them for a month. Overall I like them very much and found a lot to like about them, yet they aren’t quite perfect. I’d rate the front seat covers a 5 all considered, but the rears just a 3 (and I got them for the fronts so Ill base my rating on that).", What I like about these seat covers:, • Stitching is even; I didn’t see any unevenness or blemishes during my install, • The material itself feels thick and sturdy. It is backed with foam., • Extra pocket on the front edge of the front seats. Perfect for a phone/wallet/parking access card, • Pockets in the back of the front seats. The Tacoma seats only come with a pocket behind the passenger seat, • They don’t slide around. They fit well, have some inserts that go into the slot at the base of the seat/seat back, and have small rubber bumps on the backing. I didn’t give the back seats as thorough of a test as the front., • Sturdy zippers at the top of the front seat covers, • Front headrest covers wrap around completely, "• Sides are mostly open so you don’t have to worry about impacting the side air bags. I dont trust an aftermarket item covering up that key safety device", • The front seats seem to have a little more thickness on the sides where the bolsters are. Either this or the vinyl rather than OEM fabric gives me a more solid/cradled feeling in the seat. It feels sportier., • The color I got (black/grey) is similar to the pattern on the OEM fabric. The grey is a bit brighter and they add some openness to the cabin. It has a bolder sporty look also without being over the top., Some things to be aware of in case this matters to you:, • If you access the storage under/behind the rear seats frequently, the covers make it harder. Although there are 3 separate panels for the rear seat backs, the center panel velcros to the two side panels so you need to either fold both seats together or undo the velcro. Also since the factory seat bottoms fit together tightly, with the vinyl covers on it takes some extra tucking to make the covers fit flat where the bottoms meet., • Rear seat headrest covers just wrap over the headrests and don’t include the sides. It covers the parts that can get dirty, but doesn’t look as nice as the front headrests and are easy to bump off, • With the open sides on the front seats and the curved shape to the back, there is some looseness to the fabric. If you look you can see some of the foam backing. Most of the view of the open side and that backing is blocked by the pillar between the doors., • The pockets in the back of the front seat covers are 2 pockets; the Tacoma passenger seat had 1 longer pocket, Install notes:, • You could probably do the front seats quickly in 15 minutes or less. Installation took me about 90 minutes but I wanted it to all line up perfectly, and the back seats take a lot more effort as there are more pieces and they don’t all wrap around, • The instructions are minimal but you can figure it out., • Look at the direction of the diagonals stitching on the seat covers; I put the rear seat back covers on upside down the first time. Probably no one would notice but I swapped them anyway, • The metal clips to go under the front seat don’t have obvious connection points. On the driver’s seat I connected them to the flattish metal bar holding the motors. On the passenger seat I wrapped them around the handle to adjust the seat and then connected them to each other. Maybe you’ll find a better way., • The side straps on the rear seat backs looked different from the instructions. I fed the top/bottom strap through the single side strap

Review text: "I installed these seat covers in my ’22 Tacoma and have now been using them for a month. Overall I like them very much and found a lot to like about them, yet they aren’t quite perfect. I’d rate the front seat covers a 5 all considered, but the rears just a 3 (and I got them for the fronts so Ill base my rating on that).", What I like about these seat covers:, • Stitching is even; I didn’t see any unevenness or blemishes during my install, • The material itself feels thick and sturdy. It is backed with foam., • Extra pocket on the front edge of the front seats. Perfect for a phone/wallet/parking access card, • Pockets in the back of the front seats. The Tacoma seats only come with a pocket behind the passenger seat, • They don’t slide around. They fit well, have some inserts that go into the slot at the base of the seat/seat back, and have small rubber bumps on the backing. I didn’t give the back seats as thorough of a test as the front., • Sturdy zippers at the top of the front seat covers, • Front headrest covers wrap around completely, "• Sides are mostly open so you don’t have to worry about impacting the side air bags. I dont trust an aftermarket item covering up that key safety device", • The front seats seem to have a little more thickness on the sides where the bolsters are. Either this or the vinyl rather than OEM fabric gives me a more solid/cradled feeling in the seat. It feels sportier., • The color I got (black/grey) is similar to the pattern on the OEM fabric. The grey is a bit brighter and they add some openness to the cabin. It has a bolder sporty look also without being over the top., Some things to be aware of in case this matters to you:, • If you access the storage under/behind the rear seats frequently, the covers make it harder. Although there are 3 separate panels for the rear seat backs, the center panel velcros to the two side panels so you need to either fold both seats together or undo the velcro. Also since the factory seat bottoms fit together tightly, with the vinyl covers on it takes some extra tucking to make the covers fit flat where the bottoms meet., • Rear seat headrest covers just wrap over the headrests and don’t include the sides. It covers the parts that can get dirty, but doesn’t look as nice as the front headrests and are easy to bump off, • With the open sides on the front seats and the curved shape to the back, there is some looseness to the fabric. If you look you can see some of the foam backing. Most of the view of the open side and that backing is blocked by the pillar between the doors., • The pockets in the back of the front seat covers are 2 pockets; the Tacoma passenger seat had 1 longer pocket, Install notes:, • You could probably do the front seats quickly in 15 minutes or less. Installation took me about 90 minutes but I wanted it to all line up perfectly, and the back seats take a lot more effort as there are more pieces and they don’t all wrap around, • The instructions are minimal but you can figure it out., • Look at the direction of the diagonals stitching on the seat covers; I put the rear seat back covers on upside down the first time. Probably no one would notice but I swapped them anyway, • The metal clips to go under the front seat don’t have obvious connection points. On the driver’s seat I connected them to the flattish metal bar holding the motors. On the passenger seat I wrapped them around the handle to adjust the seat and then connected them to each other. Maybe you’ll find a better way., • The side straps on the rear seat backs looked different from the instructions. I fed the top/bottom strap through the single side strap

Review text: BALLIOL Pickup Seats Covers Compatible with Toyota Tacoma 2005-2023 SR SR5 TRD Off-Road TRD Pro TRD Sport Trall Special Edition Faux Leather(Black,5 Sets Full Seat), My husband’s job takes him to a lot of construction sites and our Toyota Tacoma has become his office on the road. With all his equipment being moved in and out of the truck, it looked like it was a construction site too. I ordered these seat covers to protect the fabric on the seats from being damaged and getting any dirtier. I am amazed at the difference. They make the truck look new again., The covers are soft and padded, making the ride more comfortable. They fit quite well too. The instructions were very clear and easy to follow. The only problem that I had was reaching around the seat to clasp the elastic strap because my arms are short. Likewise, the headrest covers went on with ease. There were no shortcuts taken in the design of these covers. They secure to the seat in multiple ways, ensuring that they will not slide around. These include chucks that slip between the seat bottom and back, the elastic strap that goes around the seat back, and hooks that go under the seat. Rather than simply putting a slit at the top for the headrest to be inserted, there are zippers to keep the top protected. Both seat covers have pockets in the back, as well as a small pocket in the front that is behind your legs. It’s a great spot for putting the money you might need for road tolls or parking lots. No fumbling around for the money., I have not yet put on the back seat covers because there is too much equipment in the way. It seems that these caused the most problems for other reviewers, so I will update my review when I try those out., These are not inexpensive covers, but they are well worth the cost.

Review text: I spend a lot of time in my car, including road trips and car camping.  I’ve been looking for something that would provide my front seats with some protection from small spills, food, dust, and dirt.  I saw these and thought I would try them., These covers fit my seats perfectly.  I have a 2023 Chevy Traverse and the head rests go up and down, but they don’t come off.  These seat covers come in two sections, the car seat cover, and a separate headrest cover.  This allows you to easily adjust the headrest to whatever position you want.  A one-piece cover makes it difficult, if not impossible, to adjust your headrest. I ordered the black, gray, and mint green cover and I really like the pop of color that these covers provide to the inside of my SUV., I rated these a 4 because these covers offer no real protection from liquids (not even water resistant), so if you spill a drink on them, it will soak through (I tested them with water).  I will probably spray some Scotch Guard waterproofing, or another fabric protector, on these seat covers to add some extra protection.

Review text: Picked up a 2014 Laramie Longhorn 1500 in mint condition.  I ordered these on a whim to protect my investment from the dog scratching up the seats while on vacation.  My order came on time, as expected.  Now...I'm a bit impressed here, I have to say the covers fit perfectly and certainly look amazing!  I ordered these in brown, in hopes they would match the color description as shown in picture, as I have saddle leather and wood trim... or at least get close...I'm total OCD with matching colors!  I was a bit blown away as the brown looks stunning in the truck!  Just a tad lighter than my saddle-colored leather seats however, the slight offset in colors adds a very nice luxurious touch!  The covers are soft and by far extremely comfortable!  They kind of have that "huggy" feeling to them which I really like and will definitely make traveling more enjoyable.  They are grippy, if your wearing shorts you will stick slightly to them which IMO...IS totally normal for any kind of leather or leather types of material!  Dont like grippy...order cloth! Installing them took about 40 minutes for me.  Both front covers went on fast and fit perfectly..better than I expected!  I did scratch my head bit bit in reference to installing the rear seat covers and the "chucks" they give you to secure the cover to the bottom/back of the seat.  description stated to attach the chuck to the loop under the cover, then push the chuck and loop through the back gap of the seat and place them upright.  Well that works just fine until you lift the seat again, then they come loose.  My only complaint is those goofy chucks!  I improvised and attached them to the bottom strap under the seat so they wont ever pop back out of the seat/bench gap again. I am extremely pleased with my purchase!  I left the "durability" part of this blank for the moment as I just received them and wanted to get a review out for my purchase.  I will update with a durability remark when we come back from all our vacations....but very please so far!

Review text: Picked up a 2014 Laramie Longhorn 1500 in mint condition.  I ordered these on a whim to protect my investment from the dog scratching up the seats while on vacation.  My order came on time, as expected.  Now...I'm a bit impressed here, I have to say the covers fit perfectly and certainly look amazing!  I ordered these in brown, in hopes they would match the color description as shown in picture, as I have saddle leather and wood trim... or at least get close...I'm total OCD with matching colors!  I was a bit blown away as the brown looks stunning in the truck!  Just a tad lighter than my saddle-colored leather seats however, the slight offset in colors adds a very nice luxurious touch!  The covers are soft and by far extremely comfortable!  They kind of have that "huggy" feeling to them which I really like and will definitely make traveling more enjoyable.  They are grippy, if your wearing shorts you will stick slightly to them which IMO...IS totally normal for any kind of leather or leather types of material!  Dont like grippy...order cloth! Installing them took about 40 minutes for me.  Both front covers went on fast and fit perfectly..better than I expected!  I did scratch my head bit bit in reference to installing the rear seat covers and the "chucks" they give you to secure the cover to the bottom/back of the seat.  description stated to attach the chuck to the loop under the cover, then push the chuck and loop through the back gap of the seat and place them upright.  Well that works just fine until you lift the seat again, then they come loose.  My only complaint is those goofy chucks!  I improvised and attached them to the bottom strap under the seat so they wont ever pop back out of the seat/bench gap again. I am extremely pleased with my purchase!  I left the "durability" part of this blank for the moment as I just received them and wanted to get a review out for my purchase.  I will update with a durability remark when we come back from all our vacations....but very please so far!

I was a bit blown away as the brown looks stunning in the truck!  Just a tad lighter than my saddle-colored leather seats however, the slight offset in colors adds a very nice luxurious touch!  The covers are soft and by far extremely comfortable!  They kind of have that "huggy" feeling to them which I really like and will definitely make traveling more enjoyable.  They are grippy, if your wearing shorts you will stick slightly to them which IMO...IS totally normal for any kind of leather or leather types of material!  Dont like grippy...order cloth! Installing them took about 40 minutes for me.  Both front covers went on fast and fit perfectly..better than I expected!  I did scratch my head bit bit in reference to installing the rear seat covers and the "chucks" they give you to secure the cover to the bottom/back of the seat.  description stated to attach the chuck to the loop under the cover, then push the chuck and loop through the back gap of the seat and place them upright.  Well that works just fine until you lift the seat again, then they come loose.  My only complaint is those goofy chucks!  I improvised and attached them to the bottom strap under the seat so they wont ever pop back out of the seat/bench gap again. I am extremely pleased with my purchase!  I left the "durability" part of this blank for the moment as I just received them and wanted to get a review out for my purchase.  I will update with a durability remark when we come back from all our vacations....but very please so far!
